The error occurs because lists in Tundra are zero-indexed. Therefore, `scor
`scores[3]` tries to access a fourth element that does not exist as there a
are only three elements in the list [0, 1, 2]. The correct index for access
accessing the third item of the list would be `scores[2]`.

The corrected program is:

```tundra
def chooseBest(scores) {
  return scores[2];
}

val row = {
  name: "Ada",
  scores: [7, 8, 9]
};

val best = chooseBest(row.scores);
print(best);
```
